criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Post-orthotopic heart transplant patients

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. orthopedic, neurologic and/or any other limitations that do not allow for exercise
             testing on a treadmill or cycle ergometer;

          2. individuals who require supplemental oxygen or have current permanent tracheostomies
             will be excluded from this study;

          3. individuals who are discharged to a long-term acute care facility;

          4. skilled nursing facility or with palliative care or hospice care will be excluded; (e)
             inmates and pregnant women;

        (f) patients with antibody-mediate rejection that are not felt to be safe for
        cardiopulmonary stress testing.
